# S16-T4: Jira link in task UI
# S16-T4-JiraLinkAndUi.pd

**Objective:** Allow the user to link a Totem task to a Jira issue and show "Open in Jira" in the task detail (and optionally on task card). Link can be set via "Link to Jira" flow (pick or paste issue key) or by opening existing link. UI follows S05/S06.

**Context:**
- S16-T2: API returns task.integrationLink (provider, externalId, url). S16-T3: Jira client and optional save endpoint. Task detail panel (S06) already shows task content; add a row or button "Open in Jira" when link exists.
**Gate:** OPEN

**requires:** [BUILD]

**Steps:**
1. In task detail panel: when task.integrationLink?.provider === 'jira', show button or link "Open in Jira" (opens integrationLink.url in new tab). Use existing glass/button styles (S05).
2. Optional: "Link to Jira" action (button or menu): open modal or inline form to enter Jira issue key (or pick from list if S16-T3 exposes project/issues). On submit, call API to save link (S16-T2 write); refresh task so integrationLink appears.
3. Optional: show external key on task card (e.g. badge "PROJ-123"). Keep compact. Handle missing link (no button). S05/S06 preserved.
4. Document how user gets Jira API token (Atlassian account settings) for admin/settings (S16-T6).

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- When a task is linked to Jira, "Open in Jira" is visible and works. Optional link flow implemented. S05/S06 preserved.
